Re: Difficulty: More nodes active, or faster nodes?

Bitcointalk

2010-08-18 18:01:40 UTC - [11]Original Post

   The performance numbers posted from a VIA C7ʼs hardware SHA-256 werenʼt
   astronomical.  Only in the 1500 khash/s range.  If you think about it,
   just because itʼs implemented in hardware doesnʼt mean itʼs crazy
   fast.  It still has to do all the steps.  Itʼs only if simplifying it
   down to single-purpose hardware makes it small enough to fit many in
   parallel.  Thatʼs not necessarily easy or a given.
